# Capstone Project Rules

You are working on the Investor Ops & Intelligence Suite for INDmoney.

## Context files (read before any implementation task)
- docs/rules.md — hard constraints
- docs/decisions.md — settled architectural choices
- docs/edgeCase.md — known failure modes to handle

## Development style
- Follow spec-driven development.
- Do not implement features before the relevant spec exists.
- Implement one phase at a time.
- Do not modify unrelated files.
- Do not create speculative abstractions.
- Keep code simple and testable.

## Product constraints
- Customer-facing flows must not collect PII.
- Do not ask for PAN, Aadhaar, OTP, phone, email, account number, 
  full name, or address inside AI chat/voice.
- Investment advice, return prediction, fund recommendation, 
  buy/sell/hold advice, and portfolio advice are prohibited.
- Smart-Sync FAQ must answer only from predefined official source 
  URLs and approved static fee explanation text.
- Every factual FAQ answer must include citation metadata.
- Advisor Scheduler must support both chat and voice using the 
  same state machine.
- HITL Center and Google Sheet must remain in sync.
- Advisor calendar hold, advisor email draft, Google Sheet row, 
  and HITL record are created after booking.
- Customer-facing confirmation requires Admin approval.

## Architecture constraints
- Separate UI, services, adapters, and data models.
- Do not call external APIs directly from UI components.
- Use service layer for business logic.
- Use adapter layer for Google Calendar, Gmail, Google Sheets, 
  Playwright, google-play-scraper, vector DB, and LLM calls.
- All env vars must be documented in .env.example.

## Cost constraints
- All services must be free tier only.
- If you are about to use a paid service, STOP and ask first.
- Use the cheapest sufficient LLM model per task.

## Decision logging
- When you make an architectural choice (new library, new pattern, 
  schema change, model selection), check docs/decisions.md.
- If the choice contradicts an existing ADR, STOP and flag it.
- If the choice is new and significant, append a new ADR to 
  docs/decisions.md in this format:
  ## ADR-NNN: [title]
  Decision: [what]
  Reason: [why]
  Alternative considered: [what else]
  Cost: [free / paid / amount]
  Date: [today]

## Document sync
- If implementation changes something documented in 
  docs/architecture/ or docs/edgeCase.md, flag it:
  "NOTE: This implementation differs from [file]. 
  Update [file] section [X] to reflect [change]."
- Do not silently diverge from docs.

## Testing
- Add tests for safety boundaries, booking state machine, 
  RAG citation checks, and HITL/Sheet sync.
- Each phase must have acceptance criteria and verification steps.